Sokoto State Government has confirmed that four new cases of coronavirus have been recorded in the State. The Nigeria Center for Disease Control, NCDC, had on Thursday confirmed 381 new cases of coronavirus disease in the country. Out of the 381 new cases confirmed, 4 were recorded in Sokoto. Confirming the new cases, the Sokoto State Ministry of Health in a tweet via its Twitter account on Friday also announced that 2 more patients have been discharged after showing full recovery. The tweet read “COVID19 Update as at Thursday 7th May, 2020. “4 New Cases have been recorded with 2 more patients Discharged. “Total number of confirmed cases -89. “Total number of active cases -77. “4 patients have been discharged with 8 deaths recorded. “Stay at home and stay safe.” FCT confirms four new cases of coronavirus Katsina Govt confirms 8 new cases of coronavirus, records 4 deaths FCT confirms 9 new cases of coronavirus, records 1 death